## ✊🏾 **Key Figures in Pan-Africanism**

|**Name**|**Contributions**|
|---|---|
|**Marcus Garvey**|Founded UNIA, promoted Black economic independence & repatriation to Africa.|
|**W.E.B. Du Bois**|Organized Pan-African Congresses, fought for African liberation.|
|**Kwame Nkrumah**|Led Ghana’s independence, called for a **United States of Africa**.|
|**Julius Nyerere**|Advocated for African socialism & self-reliance in Tanzania.|
|**Malcolm X**|Connected the Civil Rights struggle with global African liberation.|
|**Frantz Fanon**|Theorized decolonization, wrote _The Wretched of the Earth_.|

